  "Summers in Arizona are typically hot and dry": "",
  "It is raining outside right now": "",
  "A thunderstorm is approaching from the west": "",
  "Tomorrow's high will be 25 degrees C": "",
  "Describing typical seasonal conditions over many years is a climate statement, while specific short-term conditions like today's rain or tomorrow's temperature are weather descriptions.": "",
  "The two most important factors used to describe both weather and climate are:": "",
  "Humidity and cloud cover": "",
  "UV index and visibility": "",
  "Wind and pressure": "",
